Summary:        RELP Library
Name:           librelp
Version:        1.2.17
Release:        1%{?dist}
License:        GPLv3+
URL:            http://www.librelp.com
Source0:        http://download.rsyslog.com/librelp/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz
%define sha1 librelp=701d69e7723fe614b96750af8cba5ee9a54085fe
Group:          System Environment/Libraries
Vendor:         VMware, Inc.
Distribution:   Photon
BuildRequires:  gnutls-devel
BuildRequires:  autogen
Requires:       gnutls
Requires:       gmp
%description
Librelp is an easy to use library for the RELP protocol. RELP (stands
for Reliable Event Logging Protocol) is a general-purpose, extensible
logging protocol.

%package devel
Summary:        Development libraries and header files for librelp
Requires:       librelp

%description devel
The package contains libraries and header files for
developing applications that use librelp.

%prep
%setup -q
autoreconf -fiv
%build
./configure \
        --prefix=%{_prefix}
make %{?_smp_mflags}
%install
make DESTDIR=%{buildroot} install
%check
make -k check |& tee %{_specdir}/%{name}-check-log || %{nocheck}
%post   -p /sbin/ldconfig
%postun -p /sbin/ldconfig
%files
%defattr(-,root,root)
%{_libdir}/*.so.*
%{_libdir}/*.la
%{_libdir}/*.a
%files devel
%defattr(-,root,root)
%{_includedir}/*.h
%{_libdir}/*.so
%{_libdir}/pkgconfig/*.pc
